            "title": "SeederDeBoer Master Thesis Award 2020",
            "description": "I received the SeederDeBoer Master Thesis Award 2020 for my master's thesis called \"Donating to the one who stands representative of many: How adapting a practice-oriented perspective influences the inner workings of the identifiable victim effect\". I wrote this thesis during my MSc in Marketing at Radboud University, and received a grade 9/10.\n\nThe SeederDeBoer Master Thesis Award aims to inspire outstanding research with a clear link between theory and practice in the broadest sense. The MSc students of all eight Business Administration specializations at Radboud University are eligible to be nominated. My thesis was first selected by a committee of academics from various disciplines as one of the three best master's theses of the year. I won the award by competing against two other nominees in pitching my research in front of a large audience consisting of academics, professionals, and students.",
